    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. some of my more conservative students might bring up the critique that substantive due process is basically just \"judicial activism\" where judges make up rights that aren't explicitly in the Constitution. how should I address that? should i explain why that viewpoint is generally seen as a way to undermine civil rights?",
